            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>\n  By Elias Schisgall </p><br/><p>\n  Broadcom will sell $4.5 billion of senior notes to a group of underwriters led by Bank of America and JPMorgan. </p><!-- Article --><p>\n\n  The semiconductor manufacturer said Tuesday that it will use the proceeds from the sale for general corporate purposes and debt repayment. </p><p>\n\n  The transaction includes $750 million worth of 4.3% interest rate notes due 2031, as well as $1.25 billion each of 4.6% notes due 2033, 4.95% notes due 2036, and 5.7% notes due 2056, the company said. </p><br/><p>\n  Write to Elias Schisgall at elias.schisgall@wsj.com </p><br/><p>\n  (END) Dow Jones Newswires</p><p>\n\n  01-13-26 1635ET</p></div>",
